threats.description: Users may be susceptible to privilege elevation during the authentication process. This could put the client’ (Sensitive) Personally Identifiable Information unprotected from unauthorized access.
threats.mitigation:
Principle of Least Privilege.
Password policies.
Carefully manage privileged accounts.
Reviewing and auditing.
Temporary credentials.

threats.title: New STRIDE threat
threats.description: If SPII is disclosed through this process this could be detrimental to the customers, the data and the reputation of SpendSmart. An API endpoint might inadvertently exposes sensitive user data.
threats.mitigation:
Create custom error messages that reveal minimal information about the tech infrastructure. 
Log errors securely to aid in troubleshooting without compromising security.
API security.
Principle of Least Privilege.

threats.title: New STRIDE threat
threats.description: Imitating a valid admin user could make SPII available to unauthorized individuals. An attacker uses stolen API keys to access restricted endpoints.
threats.mitigation:
Session timeouts.
Packet filtering.
HTTPS or SSH connections.

threats.title: New STRIDE threat
threats.description: An attacker could perform packet flooding to overload the server and make the user interface unavailable a potentially impact healthcare operations.
threats.mitigation:
Create redundant services.
Load balancing.
Content Delivery Networks (CDNs).
Rate limiting.

threats.title: New STRIDE threat
threats.description: Risks of unauthorized elevation of user privileges, leading to inaccurate, inconsistent, unauthorized review processes.
threats.mitigation: Enforce principle of least privilege and privilege management tools.

threats.title: New STRIDE threat
threats.description: An attacker intercepts and alters data being transmitted between the client and the server.
threats.mitigation: Use HTTPS/TLS to encrypt data in transit and implement strong integrity checks.

threats.title: New STRIDE threat
threats.description: An attacker overloads the API, making it unavailable to legitimate users.
threats.mitigation:
Implement rate limiting
Use Web Application Firewalls (WAFs).
Create redundant services.
